Look who is here.

19
00:03:21,340 --> 00:03:22,340
Hi.

20
00:03:23,050 --> 00:03:24,140
About time, isn't it?

21
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,890
I'm not feeling well.

22
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:32,390
Seriously, what's up with this?

23
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:36,440
Where have you been
and what have you been doing these days?

24
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,980
You've got a lot alarms recently
and you didn't come home or go to the doctor.

25
00:03:38,980 --> 00:03:40,820
I was at Jin Woo's.

26
00:03:41,740 --> 00:03:42,760
At Balgeum's?

27
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:45,780
No.

28
00:03:46,490 --> 00:03:48,200
Not Balgeum? Then which friend?

29
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,160
You don't know him.

30
00:03:51,330 --> 00:03:54,120
What's wrong with you?

31
00:03:55,130 --> 00:03:57,960
Gi Seop, tell me what's wrong. Come on.

32
00:03:59,590 --> 00:04:00,840
I'm just not feeling well.

33
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,090
Were you not feeling well
at that friend's place the whole time?

34
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:07,930
Stay still.

35
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,100
Ouch!

36
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:18,440
My heart just started beating faster.

37
00:04:20,730 --> 00:04:21,780
I'll get some medicine.

38
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,450
I must've been.

39
00:04:29,030 --> 00:04:30,582
I must've been unwell the whole time.

40
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:36,750
You seemed okay for a while.
I should've paid more attention.

41
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:40,960
Stop by at the school first.
You know what you need to do there, right?

42
00:04:42,590 --> 00:04:43,670
Why do I have to go to the school?

43
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,760
Stop goofing around.

44
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:49,430
We have less than 15 days left
before going to the US.

45
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:52,930
Go get the documents
that I told you about from the school.

46
00:04:52,930 --> 00:04:55,770
I'll pick you up from school.
Let's go see a doctor.

47
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:56,810
The US?

48
00:04:56,810 --> 00:04:57,860
Listen to you.

49
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,190
Gosh. The US?

50
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,910
Seriously, did something happen?

51
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,580
[Today's to-do list]

52
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:03,800
[Recruitment Briefing Session for International
and Exchange Students to the US]

53
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:05,550
[2024 Study Abroad Guide]

54
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:12,390
The person in charge is on the phone,
so you have to wait a little.

55
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:14,510
Please have a seat and wait.

56
00:06:31,780 --> 00:06:33,780
[Immigrating to the US]

57
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:50,680
Hey, do you remember this day?
You and Kim Jin Woo are in it. Wow, hilarious.

58
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:56,180
I've got something to say to you.

59
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,270
Let me tell you now.

60
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:03,860
I wonder why I wasn't brave enough
to ask you out.

61
00:07:05,820 --> 00:07:08,490
Go for it.

62
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:11,456
Go for it.

63
00:07:11,456 --> 00:07:14,400
Go for it.

64
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,660
Go for it.

65
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:19,910
I like you. Would you like to go out with me?

66
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:23,552
Accept. Accept.

67
00:07:23,552 --> 00:07:26,250
Accept. Accept.

68
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:49,740
[He's looking at someone so romantically.
But who is he looking at?]

69
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,500
I've seen

70
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:02,330
this gaze a lot somewhere.

71
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:05,750
It's the way you look at someone

72
00:08:07,380 --> 00:08:08,380
you like!

73
00:08:15,180 --> 00:08:16,300
I like him.

74
00:08:17,410 --> 00:08:19,010
Okay, Mr. Jeong Gi Seop. Mr. Jeong Gi Seop.

75
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:24,980
He… He

76
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,730
likes him, right?

77
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:30,150
Do you? Do you like him?

78
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:39,580
I'm not capable of liking anyone,

79
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,460
but maybe I like him.

80
00:08:45,460 --> 00:08:47,210
Yes, if you like him that much,
you should tell him.

81
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,380
I'm going now.

82
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:54,340
Are you Mr. Jeong Gi Seop
who wants to discuss studying abroad?

83
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:55,840
- Let's get started right away.
- I'm sorry.

84
00:08:57,182 --> 00:09:00,560
Please excuse me.
I'm the type that never says "no,"

85
00:09:01,770 --> 00:09:05,020
but I have to confess my feelings to someone.
I need to go. I'm sorry.

86
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:06,900
But we can

87
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:07,980
get started right away.

88
00:09:10,610 --> 00:09:13,360
You won't be loved by anyone.

89
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,900
So in the end, you won't be loved by anyone.

90
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:21,490
I don't care if no one loves me in the end.

91
00:09:22,540 --> 00:09:27,830
The important thing is
the fact that I like Kim Jin Woo.

92
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:31,920
Kim Jin Woo.

93
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:48,730
The subscriber you are calling
is not available…

94
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,560
What's going on?

95
00:10:03,540 --> 00:10:04,580
Who are you?

96
00:10:06,830 --> 00:10:07,870
What about you?

97
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:10,630
I'm Jeong Gi Seop.

98
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:11,630
What?

99
00:10:13,590 --> 00:10:14,630
What's your problem?

100
00:10:18,930 --> 00:10:23,430
I don't know who you are,
but you can't just come into Jin Woo's place.

101
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:24,680
Jin Woo?

102
00:10:27,180 --> 00:10:28,270
Oh! You're

103
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:30,100
Jin Woo's friend, right?

104
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,310
Yes.

105
00:10:32,310 --> 00:10:33,360
I see.

106
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:35,780
Seriously, who are you?

107
00:10:35,780 --> 00:10:38,490
I own this place, you punk.

108
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:40,070
Got that?

109
00:10:40,990 --> 00:10:43,120
I see. Okay. Hello.

110
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:46,240
Yes, hello. Nice to meet you.

111
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,410
Did something happen to Jin Woo?

112
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:51,070
Sorry?

113
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:55,880
His father kept calling me
saying he couldn't reach him. Gosh.

114
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:58,220
It doesn't look like
he came home last night, either.

115
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:00,720
Do you know where he is?

116
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,260
He never does that.

117
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:03,850
Tell me about it. Gosh.

118
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:09,600
Hello?

119
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:13,020
Yes. Go ahead.

120
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:18,110
Okay, one moment please. Answer it.

121
00:11:18,110 --> 00:11:19,820
- Who is it?
- Jin Woo's father.

122
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:22,410
- His father?
- Talk to him.

123
00:11:22,410 --> 00:11:24,120
He wants to talk to you.

124
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:33,880
Hello? My name is Jeong Gi Seop… Pardon?

125
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:36,800
Sorry?

126
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:20,840
Why aren't you coming?

127
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,630
What is he talking about?

128
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,760
Hello?

129
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:28,850
Yes, hello?

130
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:32,020
Hey, I'm at the theater. Where are you?

131
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:36,810
Really? I'm on the fourth floor
at the entrance of Cinema Six. Do you see me?

132
00:12:36,810 --> 00:12:37,810
What?

133
00:12:41,070 --> 00:12:42,780
But the entrance to Cinema Six
is on the second floor.

134
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:45,530
No way. Hold on.

135
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:51,790
I'm sorry. I'll be right there.

136
00:12:51,790 --> 00:12:54,330
They have Seogyeong
and Seogyeong Jungang locations.

137
00:12:54,330 --> 00:12:56,040
I mistakenly came to Seogyeong Jungang instead.

138
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,340
I'll send you the reservation,
so start watching first. I'll be right there.

139
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:01,000
No, I'll just wait for you here.

140
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,460
It's okay. Just start watching it first.

141
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:04,170
Should we cancel this one
and reserve the next one?

142
00:13:04,170 --> 00:13:05,720
No, don't. I said just go in first.

143
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,760
No, it's okay to just cancel it
and reserve the next one.

144
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:30,620
What are you doing out here?

145
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,830
I told you that I would wait for you.

146
00:13:33,830 --> 00:13:34,910
What about the movie?

147
00:13:34,910 --> 00:13:37,420
I couldn't cancel it,
so I just reserved the next one.

148
00:13:40,170 --> 00:13:41,340
Did you sprint here?

149
00:13:45,630 --> 00:13:46,720
Let's take our time.

150
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:49,550
Aren't you thirsty?
Should we get a soda and popcorn too?

151
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:52,510
Okay.

152
00:13:52,510 --> 00:13:54,220
Which popcorn flavor do you like?

153
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:56,690
I'll buy. Let's go.

154
00:14:59,830 --> 00:15:02,080
[Jeong Gi Seop, I'm on my way to Hoengseong now.
I have something to tell you when I meet you.]

155
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,210
[Jeong Gi Seop missed call]

156
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:12,300
Hello?

157
00:15:16,140 --> 00:15:17,220
Sorry?

158
00:15:19,140 --> 00:15:22,850
Jeong Gi Seop is on his way to our house,
you mean, to Hoengseong?

159
00:15:29,740 --> 00:15:33,990
The subscriber you are calling
is not available…

160
00:15:33,990 --> 00:15:35,910
It's still powered off.

161
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:58,520
I'm sorry about earlier.
I don't know why I got the location mixed up.

162
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:00,980
Gosh, why did I do that?

163
00:16:00,980 --> 00:16:02,730
It's nice to take a walk like this.

164
00:16:04,690 --> 00:16:06,560
We're almost at the restaurant.
It's right around the corner.

165
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:10,050
Okay. Let's take a walk again after we eat.

166
00:16:10,690 --> 00:16:11,700
Aren't you going to be cold?

167
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:12,700
You're by my side.

168
00:16:19,370 --> 00:16:21,580
Wow, the ambiance is great.

169
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:24,040
Do you think so? I'm glad.

170
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:27,790
Hello. May I take your order, please?

171
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:30,340
Well, what would you like to eat?

172
00:16:32,340 --> 00:16:33,630
This one.

173
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:34,760
One is enough?

174
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:35,760
Yes.

175
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,180
Let's also order these two.

176
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:38,430
Okay.

177
00:16:38,430 --> 00:16:42,230
We'll order these three. Anything to drink?

178
00:16:42,230 --> 00:16:43,230
Okay.

179
00:16:45,980 --> 00:16:47,860
Can we also have these two?

180
00:16:47,860 --> 00:16:49,520
Okay. We'll bring them right away.

181
00:16:52,190 --> 00:16:54,240
You did that last time too.
You ordered a lot again.

182
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:55,320
Eat them up.

183
00:16:56,450 --> 00:16:58,780
If we get sleepy after eating again,
should we just stay here?

184
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:00,620
That's a bit…

185
00:17:01,910 --> 00:17:03,200
I need to use the restroom.

186
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,210
Okay.

187
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:16,380
[Coupon 80,000 won]

188
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,780
Weren't you using the restroom?

189
00:17:32,780 --> 00:17:34,490
I stepped out for a second.

190
00:17:38,620 --> 00:17:41,700
It's my gift to you.
Thanks so much for everything today.

191
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,080
A gift?

192
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,290
I got another one when I was buying mine.

193
00:17:46,660 --> 00:17:48,460
You can't really check your messages
when you're doing your part-time work.

194
00:17:48,460 --> 00:17:52,050
I want to check your messages right away too.
I asked a nearby place to hold it for me,

195
00:17:52,050 --> 00:17:53,170
so that I can surprise you.

196
00:18:07,890 --> 00:18:10,020
Your food is ready.

197
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:17,570
Balgeum, it looks delicious. Let's enjoy it.

198
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:21,950
Enjoy your food.

199
00:18:25,290 --> 00:18:26,910
Are you okay? Is something going on?

200
00:18:28,790 --> 00:18:31,920
I never asked you for this.

201
00:18:32,670 --> 00:18:34,420
Come on. I just wanted you to have it--

202
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:35,420
I don't need things like this.

203
00:18:45,270 --> 00:18:47,560
You barely ate anything.

204
00:18:48,980 --> 00:18:51,310
My stomach feels a little funny.

205
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,690
- Shall we go now?
- Okay.

206
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:05,410
Please charge this card.

207
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:07,160
That would be 83,000 won.

208
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,160
Pardon?

209
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:11,040
Isn't it 79,000 won?

210
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:15,550
You ordered three dishes and two drinks.
So the total is 83,000 won.

211
00:19:15,550 --> 00:19:17,760
No way.

212
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,938
Can I see your menu again? I'm sure--

213
00:19:28,938 --> 00:19:30,020
One moment.

214
00:19:30,020 --> 00:19:31,100
Please use this one.

215
00:19:33,310 --> 00:19:36,190
But I'm sure I saw it correctly.

216
00:19:36,190 --> 00:19:39,280
Thank you for the food.
I really enjoyed it, Balgeum.

217
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,120
Choi Balgeum.

218
00:19:50,410 --> 00:19:53,290
We finished eating too quickly.
Where should we go next?

219
00:19:55,710 --> 00:19:58,500
Do you want to go get a drink?
We never had a drink together.

220
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:02,510
I looked up a bar nearby
and it had a good ambiance.

221
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:06,600
You don't feel like going to a bar?

222
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:10,350
Then should we just go home?

223
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:12,600
We can just get some drinks
from a convenience store and drink at home--

224
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,600
Shouldn't you go home?

225
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,850
What?

226
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:19,320
You didn't quit piano, right?
When are you going back?

227
00:20:20,940 --> 00:20:22,900
You should go back to your house, not mine.

228
00:20:28,870 --> 00:20:30,250
Should I quit piano

229
00:20:31,410 --> 00:20:33,410
and just stay here with you?

230
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:37,840
- I like the way things are now--
- No.

231
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:44,510
I don't like the way things are now. Go back.

232
00:20:50,060 --> 00:20:51,180
Sorry. I'll get going first.

233
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:54,140
Choi Balgeum.

234
00:20:58,650 --> 00:20:59,820
Choi Balgeum.

235
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:05,280
Let's just end this.

236
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:08,240
What's the matter with you today?

237
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,410
It's not just today.

238
00:21:11,660 --> 00:21:13,500
I knew it wouldn't work from the beginning.

239
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:14,960
I shouldn't have started it.

240
00:21:16,290 --> 00:21:17,750
Is it because I didn't go ahead
and watch the movie first?

241
00:21:17,750 --> 00:21:20,550
Or because I can't eat much?
If not, because of the gift?

242
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:23,340
Just tell me and I'll change.
I'll do as you say.

243
00:21:23,340 --> 00:21:24,880
It's not like that.

244
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,760
Then what is it?
How would I know if you don't tell me?

245
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:30,390
I can't just let you go again like this
without even knowing why.

246
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:32,020
It's because I feel ashamed.

247
00:21:33,140 --> 00:21:36,390
I feel ashamed that I'm broke
and that my family has become poor.

248
00:21:38,190 --> 00:21:40,860
I'm struggling to earn
a meager income to be with you

249
00:21:40,860 --> 00:21:42,030
and to spend a day together.

250
00:21:43,860 --> 00:21:47,280
But I'm even ashamed to be happy for a second
when I received an expensive gift.

251
00:21:49,620 --> 00:21:50,950
It was the same back then.

252
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:55,870
I was ashamed that my family had become poor.
That was the reason.

253
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,000
Ji In Ho.

254
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:06,340
I still like you.
I lied when I said I didn't like you.

255
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:09,640
I still like you so much,

256
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:12,390
but I really hate myself.

257
00:22:13,850 --> 00:22:15,680
I really hate myself for being like this.

258
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:17,480
Choi Balgeum.

259
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:19,310
I hate myself even more when I'm with you.

260
00:22:19,310 --> 00:22:20,650
Even this moment.

261
00:22:23,650 --> 00:22:25,400
So…

262
00:22:28,610 --> 00:22:31,820
So, please. Let's just end it here.

263
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:12,680
